						<summary>

						<p>This is a fragment of a Koṅgu inscription with another of a Pāṇḍya king and a third dated in the 11th year of a king (name lost), The first records the gift of a lamp by one Pūmaṉ Araiyaṉ to the temple of Nachchiṉāṟkiṉiyār. The second seems to provide for offerings and a lamp in the shrine of Tirukkāmakkōṭṭa. nāchchiyār in the same temple.</p>						

						</summary>
